<%# Admin nav region (Task 10, Navigation IA skeleton). Gated at the call
    site on current_grant.admin? (app/helpers/application_helper.rb), not
    here — this partial assumes it should render.

    Phases 4-8 populate the panel with real admin navigation; until then
    this is a genuinely empty, accessible region (not a dead link, not a
    "coming soon" placeholder) so the affordance's shape — a labeled
    navigation landmark — is stable across phases and doesn't need
    reshaping once content lands.

    Desktop gets an interactive disclosure (reuses the existing `dropdown`
    Stimulus controller for the click/outside-click/Escape wiring already
    proven by shared/_workspace_switcher and shared/_user_menu — no new JS).
    It deliberately does NOT use role="menu"/"menuitem" the way those two
    do: an ARIA menu with zero menuitem children fails aria-required-children,
    and there's nothing menu-shaped to put in it yet. Mobile renders as a
    static labeled group (matching the "Workspaces" mobile group style) since
    it already lives inside the collapsible hamburger accordion — a second,
    nested disclosure toggle there would be redundant. -%>
<% if local_assigns[:mobile] %>
  <nav aria-label="<%= t("navigation.admin.aria_label") %>"
       class="md:hidden px-1 pt-3 mt-1 border-t border-border">
    <p class="px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wide">
      <%= t("navigation.admin.label") %>
    </p>
    <p class="px-2 py-2 text-sm text-text-muted">
      <%= t("navigation.admin.empty") %>
    </p>
  </nav>
<% else %>
  <nav aria-label="<%= t("navigation.admin.aria_label") %>"
       data-controller="dropdown"
       class="relative hidden md:block">
    <button data-dropdown-target="button" data-action="click->dropdown#toggle"
            id="admin-nav-button" type="button"
            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="admin-nav-panel"
            class="min-h-[44px] flex items-center gap-2 px-3 rounded-lg text-text-body
                   hover:bg-surface-sunken focus-ring">
      <%= t("navigation.admin.label") %>
      <span aria-hidden="true">&#9662;</span>
    </button>

    <div data-dropdown-target="menu" id="admin-nav-panel"
         aria-labelledby="admin-nav-button"
         class="hidden absolute right-0 mt-2 w-64 rounded-lg bg-surface-raised
                border border-border shadow-lg z-50 p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><%= t("navigation.admin.empty") %></p>
    </div>
  </nav>
<% end %>
